para_trans: Regarding payment of Dearness Allowance to Special Teachers under Disability Inclusive Education Scheme (Secondary Level).
Government of Maharashtra
Department of School Education and Sports
Government Decision No: - SAAT 2025 / Q. No.05 / SD-9
Mantralaya Extension Building, Mumbai 400032
Date: 21st of March, 2025
Reference: -
1) Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune. Letter dated 31.12.2024 2) Finance Department No. Meaning 2024 / Q. No.80 / Mean-3, D. 25.07.2024 and D. Circular of 12.02.2025
The Proposal: -

According to the report of the Choksi Committee headed by Secretary, School Education and KRODA Department under Disability Inclusive Education Scheme (Secondary Level), 161 special teachers have been qualified at the government level.

Based on the information submitted at the field level for the dearness allowance of the qualified special teachers at the government level and the verification of the original documents of these special teachers by the then Deputy Director (Disability Inclusive Education Scheme), the dearness allowance of the special teachers was considered and a proposal for the dearness allowance of 155 special teachers was submitted to the government. Accordingly. As per the Government Decision dated 28.06.2023, Rs. 11,46,43, 670 / - and Rs. As per the Government Decision dated 21.09.2023, the difference in remuneration of Special Teachers is Rs. 6,22,70, 780 / - totalling to Rs. A sum of ₹450 / - has been disbursed. The original documents submitted by 4 of the remaining 6 special teachers have been verified at the level of Directorate of Primary Education, Pune and Divisional Deputy Director of Education. Upon verification, these 4 special teachers have been found to be eligible for the next Gal B. Thakat salary. It was under consideration of the Government to disburse funds to these 4 Special Teachers for payment of Dearness Allowance for the period from the date of appointment to March, 2024.
The Government's Decisions:

As per the report of the Vigilance Committee at the Government level under the Disability Inclusive Education Scheme (Secondary Level), out of 161 Special Teachers who have been qualified, 4 Special Teachers have been awarded a total amount of Rs. 68,49,024 - (Characters Rs.
Sixty-two lakh ninety-nine thousand twenty-four only) is being approved under this Government decision.

The amount of the outstanding salary should be credited to the account of the respective special teachers. The Director of Education (Primary), Pune will be held responsible if any irregularity is found in this regard.

The disbursement of funds is being approved subject to verification by the Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune, considering the admissibility of the amount of salary in the said deduction. If funds are left over after payment of salaries as mentioned above, a report should be submitted to the government. The government's prior approval should be taken before appropriating the balance funds. The utilization certificate of the funds disbursed should be submitted to the government within a period of one month.

3. Expenditure "Demand No. E-2,2202 General Education, 01 Primary Education, 106 - Teachers & Other Services, (00) (00) (01) Samagra Shiksha Abhiyan (General) (State Share Wo Percentage) (2202I 612) (Programme), 31 - Auxiliary Grants (Non-Payment) "available in this financial year 2024-25
Government Decision No: Yes 2025 / Q. No.05 / SD-1
be subtracted from the existing budgetary provision.

The funds are being handed over to the State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education, Mumbai. The Under Secretary / Cell Officer (Cash Branch / Accounts Branch), Department of School Education & Training, Mantralaya, Mumbai is being declared as the "Drawing and Disbursing Officer" and Joint Secretary / Deputy Secretary, Department of School Education & Training, Mantralaya, Mumbai as the "Controlling Officer" for the collection and disbursement of these funds. The concerned Drawing and Disbursing Officer should withdraw the funds from the treasury and deposit them in the SNA account of the Samagra Shiksha Yojana. The State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education, Mumbai should hand over the funds to the Director of Education (Primary), Maharashtra State, Pune.
5. Finance Department is fulfilling all the conditions mentioned in the Government Circular dated 12.02.2025.
The grant is a conditional grant and the terms and conditions for the same are stated in this Government Decision.

6. The said Government Decision Planning Department vide Unofficial Reference No. 56/1471, d. 30.01.2025 and the Department of Finance in the informal reference No. 244 / Expenditure - 5, D. Is being issued as agreed under 18.02.2025.
